{"lemma":"دارِيِّي","slug":"دارِيِّي","root":"د.#.ر","root_slug":"د-_-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/د-_-ر","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n12357","n13395"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%90%D9%91%D9%8A"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n12357","headword_ar":"دَارِيٌ","root":"drA^","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Coming from a place,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from a distant place, unexpectedly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA: but only the pls. of the word in this sense are there mentioned:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an enemy showing open hostility,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coming forth into the field to encounter another in battle:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a stranger:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duraA^='u","text_ar":"دُرَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dur~aA='N","text_ar":"دُرَّا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, TA.) People say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naHonu fuqaraA='u duraA^='u","text_ar":"نَحْنُ فُقَرَا=ءُ دُرَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We are poor men, come from a distant place,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strangers"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (T, TA.)       -A2-  See also 1, last sentence. ―         -b2-  [Hence,] metaphorically used by Ru-beh as meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Swollen with anger."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["T","M","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n13395","headword_ar":"دَارِىٌّ","root":"dwr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A man (A)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who keeps to his house;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who does not quit it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, A,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nor seek sustenance;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAriy~apN","text_ar":"دَارِيَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b2-  And hence, (S,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A possessor of the blessings, comforts,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conveniences, of life:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAriy~uwna","text_ar":"دَارِيُّونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) ―         -b3-  Also A camel, or sheep or goat,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that remains at the house, not going to pasture:"},{"kind":"text","text":"fem. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A:) or a camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that remains behind in the place where the others lie down;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;) and so a sheep or goat. (M.) ―         -b4-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"day~aArN","text_ar":"دَيَّارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sailor that has the charge of the sail."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A seller of perfumes:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so called in relation to Dáreen, (S, A, K,) a port of ElBahreyn, in which was a market whereto musk used to be brought from India. (S, K.) It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mavalu Aljaliysi AlS~aAliHi mavalu Ald~aAriY~i","text_ar":"مَثَلُ الجَلِيسِ الصَّالِحِ مَثَلُ الدَّارِىِّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ino lamo yuHo*ika mino EiTorihi Ealiqaka mino riyHihi","text_ar":"اـِنْ لَمْ يُحْذِكَ مِنْ عِطْرِهِ عَلِقَكَ مِنْ رِيحِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The similitude of the righteous companion who sits and converses with one is that of the seller of perfumes: if he give not to thee of his perfume, somewhat of his sweet odour clings to thee"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.)"}],"source_refs":["A","M","S","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}